    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Available is a technically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 horizontally opposed six-cylinder engine equipped with VarioCam Plus. This naturally aspirated powerplant is mated to a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, providing precise engagement and optimal gear spacing. Critical preventative maintenance has been performed, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS). The suspension geometry remains true, bolstered by Bilstein B6 dampers that maintain the chassis's legendary communicative feedback. The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers with ventilated rotors, showing excellent bite and minimal fade. While the exterior displays minor road-going patina, the mechanical vitals\u2014including oil analysis and compression figures\u2014confirm a healthy, high-revving engine ready for",
